$ Oracle: media recovery
@ media recovery

Media recovery applies → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database/files/archived-redo-log[archived redo log files] or
→ development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/backup-recovery/backup/incremental[incremental backups] to restored → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/backup-recovery/backup[backups].

A → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database cannot be opened if online data needs media recovery.

?  Media recovery is necessary after
    • restoring a → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/backup-recovery/backup of a → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database/files/data or → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database/files/control or
    • if a data file was taken offline without the `offline normal` option


Media recovery is not an automatic process: it must be started by a user 

sa:
  → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/backup-recovery/recovery/media/block
